  "The four major disciplines of oceanography are biological, chemical, geological, and physical oceanography. These branches often overlap in research and practice.": "",
  "Which branch of oceanography would study marine food webs?": "",
  "Marine food webs — the feeding relationships between organisms — fall under biological oceanography, which examines how marine organisms interact within ecosystems.": "",
  "Plate tectonics and its effects on the ocean floor are studied in which oceanographic discipline?": "",
  "Geological oceanography encompasses the study of plate tectonics, including how the movement of tectonic plates creates features like mid-ocean ridges and subduction trenches.": "",
  "Which discipline would investigate how dissolved oxygen varies with ocean depth?": "",
  "The concentration of dissolved gases, including oxygen, in seawater is a core topic in chemical oceanography.": "",
  "Water temperature and density changes in the ocean are most closely linked to which branch of oceanography?": "",
  "Physical oceanography studies the physical properties of seawater, including temperature, density, and how these factors drive ocean circulation.": "",
  "Why do the four branches of oceanography often overlap in research?": "",
  "Each discipline only addresses a single ocean basin": "",
  "They study completely unrelated phenomena": "",
  "Overlap is discouraged by the scientific community": "",
  "Ocean processes involve interactions among biology, chemistry, geology, and physics": "",
  "The ocean is a complex system where biological, chemical, geological, and physical processes constantly interact. This means oceanographic research frequently requires an interdisciplinary approach.": "",
  "What is biological oceanography?": "",
  "The study of marine organisms and their relationships within ocean ecosystems": "",
  "The study of tectonic activity beneath the seafloor": "",
  "The study of the chemical properties of seawater": "",
  "The study of wave mechanics and tidal patterns": "",
  "Biological oceanography is the branch that investigates marine organisms — from microscopic plankton to large marine mammals — and the ecological relationships that connect them.": "",
